description: This module allows the operator to choose various external reference lookup tools for inclusion in XDR Investigations. Examples may include geolocation for IP addresses, for example. This information can then be used by the XDR AI Assistant to derive patterns, anomalies, and factors of interest or potential concern in the observables found as part of an Incident

capabilities.description: Checks if the relay server is up
Provides reference/pivot links to look up additional details about the observables

tips:
1. To configure this module, you must first have installed the server code and be hosting it in an internet-accessible location. 

2. Fill out the configuration details in the form on this page.  

    a. **Optional:** Change the name of the module as it will appear in your integration lists and pivot menu etc.

    b. **Required:** Enter the URL at which the server can be reached by XDR
short_description: A reference engine and an AI assistant to provide investigative analysis into observables by referencing metadata about the observables themselves.
title: Artificial Intelligence Assisted Investigations (AIAI)
